.TH "kthread_destroy_worker" 9 "kthread_destroy_worker" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kthread_destroy_worker \- destroy a kthread worker
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" kthread_destroy_worker
.BI "(struct kthread_worker *worker "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "worker" 12
worker to be destroyed
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Flush and destroy \fIworker\fP.  The simple flush is enough because the kthread
worker API is used only in trivial scenarios.  There are no multi-step state
machines needed.
